> This Chorizo Topped Mac and Cheese is a crowd pleaser and is one to get the
> family round the dinner table for. Super simple to make, and easily customised
> to suit the kids too.

== Pasta ==

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{75%g}.

Once boiling, add the @macaroni{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil.
Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the saucepan. Drizzle with
@oil{some} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Chorizo Crumb ==

While the pasta cooks, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

When the pan is hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}
and fry until the chorizo starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Transfer the chorizo crumb to a #bowl{} and set aside. Keep the pan for later.

== Sauce ==

Pop a large saucepan on medium-high heat and add the @oil for the roux{for
the roux}.

Once the oil is hot, stir in the @plain flour{2%tsp}. Cook until it forms a paste
consistency, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Gradually stir in the @water for the sauce{250%ml} and then the @chicken stock
paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Broccoli ==

Meanwhile, wipe out your (now empty) #frying pan{} and pop back on medium-high
heat with a drizzle of @oil{some}. Halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g}
stems lengthways.

Once the pan is hot, add the broccoli and stir-fry for ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the
garlic and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Add a splash of water and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.
Lower the heat to medium and allow to cook until the broccoli is tender,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove the pan from the heat.

== Assembly ==

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, then remove
from the heat.

Add the @dried oregano{1%tsp} and Cheddar, stir until well combined. Taste and
season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{} if needed.

Add the cooked pasta to the sauce and stir to combine. TIP: Add a splash of
water to loosen if needed.

When everything is ready, spoon the mac and cheese into your #serving bowls{} and
sprinkle over the chorizo crumb.

Serve with the garlicky broccoli. Enjoy!